summary:
Behind the Scenes of The Next Doctor (Part Four) Excerpt from David Bailey’s behind-the-scenes report in DWM #404

 David...
caption:
Behind the Scenes of The Next Doctor (Part Four)

Excerpt from David Bailey’s behind-the-scenes report in DWM #404

David Tennant arrives on set to lots of excited shouts from the patient crowd. He and Velile [Tshabalala, who plays Rosita] rehearse their next scene before he grabs some grub [from the caterers] and heads out to shake hands and sign autographs.

When he returns, and before filming starts again, we squirrel ourselves in a quiet corner - far from the eager ears of the fans outside - and ask him the Big Question about this year’s Christmas Special.

“I think it’s great,” he beams.  “Because when the regular articles come around in the papers - as they do with morbid predictability - listing who’s going to be taking over from me, then David Morrissey tends to be one of the four or five names that get listed. So, I think that’s a nice gag already there. You’re sort of playing with the expectations of who he might be. I think casting David… you know, he’s the sort of actor you would hope to get. I would like to think that we’d food at least some of the people.”

What was it that made Russell [T. Davies, writer & showrunner] want to pull that kind of twist?

“Well, I didn’t really see it as a twist,” he says. “It’s simply a good story! A twist would be David Morrissey revealing in the last few seconds that he’s the Valeyard or something. I just thought it was a big, powerful concept and a different way to explore who the Doctor is, and what his heroism means, when transplanted into an ordinary man. Plus, there’s the notion of the mental fugue, which I’ve always wanted to write about, cos it fascinates me.”
